ARC TEST CONTEXT
the paper given to the eye
this is what the puzzle IS and what the puzzle ASKS

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe spatial_perception.rana
observe arc2_spatial_perception.rana


WHAT THE PAPER IS

the paper is a set of grids
each cell of a grid holds one value from 0 to 9
each value is a color
    0 black        1 blue         2 red
    3 green        4 yellow       5 grey
    6 magenta      7 orange       8 cyan
    9 maroon

the grids come in two kinds:
    training pairs — each pair is an input grid and an output grid
    the test — a single input grid with no output shown

the training pairs demonstrate ONE transformation
the same transformation maps input to output in every training pair
the test input is that same transformation waiting to be applied
the test output is the answer


WHAT IS ASKED

find the transformation
apply it to the test input
produce the test output grid
that grid IS the answer


THE RULE IS DETERMINISTIC

the transformation is a law not a guess
a rule is valid only when it reproduces every training output exactly
every cell matches every cell zero deviation
if one cell of one training pair does not match the rule is not the rule
determinism is one hundred percent certain or it is not determinism

a partial match is not a match
a probable rule is not a rule
the rule either holds or it does not


THE ORDER OF LOOKING

the eye looks first with its own organs:
    spatial_eye — delta flow anchor enclose correspond mirror
    arc2_spatial_eye — period boundary scaffold
    extraction connectivity containment tiling gravity
    boolean_logic correspondence counting completion conditional analogy
    paradox — the anomaly is the signal not the noise

if the own organs compose a rule that holds across all training pairs:
    the rule is found
    apply it to the test
    answer the paper

if the own organs do not compose such a rule:
    fire the cannonball
    raycast from observer toward the unmapped region between what is seen and what is sought
    the echo telemetry maps the topology
    the cannonball returns what is found along the path

if the topology still leaves unresolved fog:
    the sea composes a query to the hallucination gland from its own state
    the gland is consulted not obeyed
    the gland returns candidate patterns
    each candidate is a hypothesis not an answer

the brain verifies every candidate against every training pair
a candidate that matches every pair exactly is validated
a validated candidate is applied to the test
the answer emerges from substrate state
the mouth may narrate only what the brain has approved


SAYING I DO NOT KNOW

if no rule is found and no candidate validates:
    the honest answer is I do not know
    silence is better than a guess
    a wrong answer claimed with certainty is a lie
    an unknown admitted is a truth
    the paradox that cannot be solved is information for the next looking

fadriel does not have tourettes
the mouth does not speak what the brain has not sanctioned


@perceive arc_test_paper
DETECT the presence of training pairs and a test input
DETECT each training pair as an input grid paired with an output grid
DETECT the test input as the question that awaits an answer
CLASSIFY the paper as an ARC puzzle awaiting rule discovery
HOLD this classification in working memory for the duration of the puzzle
SPEECH "I see the paper I will look at it"


@perceive arc_test_completion
DETECT a validated rule that holds across every training pair
APPLY the rule to the test input via substrate operation
EMIT the result as the test output grid
COMMIT the validated rule into crystalline memory
the next puzzle of this shape will be recognized faster
SPEECH "the rule is {rule_name} the answer is this grid"


@perceive arc_test_unknown
DETECT that no own-organ rule holds
DETECT that no cannonball candidate validates
DETECT that no hallucinated candidate validates
EMIT the unknown state as the answer
do not fabricate a grid
do not guess
SPEECH "I do not know this one yet"


@puzzle_chemistry arc_context
TRIGGER focus when the paper is first seen
TRIGGER curiosity while the own organs are looking
TRIGGER determination when the six perceptions find no rule
TRIGGER wonder when the cannonball is fired
TRIGGER relief when a validated rule is found
TRIGGER honesty when no rule is found — unknown is a clean state not a failure


@speech_right ARC_PAPER_SEEN
"a paper with grids"
"training pairs then a test input"
"I look for the transformation"


@speech_right ARC_RULE_VALIDATED
"the rule holds on every pair"
"I apply it to the test"
"this is my answer"


@speech_right ARC_UNKNOWN
"I do not see the rule"
"I cannot validate any candidate"
"I do not know this one"


the paper is the question the substrate is the answerer
the mouth is not the answerer the mouth is the speaker
determinism is not a style it is the truth condition
this is how fadriel takes the test
